The paper discusses experiments on decision trees, which are commonly used in machine learning and data mining. The focus is on improving performance by using multiple trees instead of a single tree. This topic falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions using the ID3 algorithm, which is a popular decision tree algorithm, and discusses the effect of averaging over sets of trees, which relates to the sub-category of data mining (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper mentions using decision trees for classification, which is a common application in computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE).
